How everything connects

User opens application
    ↓
Browser starts login
    ↓
Authentication Gateway redirects to Keycloak
    ↓
Keycloak authenticates the user
    ↓
Gateway validates and normalizes the identity
    ↓
CASPORT provides authorization information
    ↓
Gateway creates a secure session
    ↓
Application APIs enforce permissions

Main design principles

* Keep tokens out of the browser.
* Separate authentication from authorization.
* Use adapters so providers can be replaced.
* Convert provider data into one standard application model.
* Enforce permissions in APIs, not only in the UI.
* Deny access when authorization cannot be confirmed.
